subSubSection.paragraph:
Type host.
Grey catbird,
Dumetella carolinensis (Linnaeus)
( Passeriformes : Mimidae ).

Type locality.
Adams County, Pennsylvania, USA .

Remarks. This species was originally described as
Cyclocoelum dumetellae
Zeliff, 1943
, but it was considered to be a synonym of
Cyclocoelum ( Hyptiasmus ) elongatum
Harrah, 1921
by
Dubois ( 1959 )
.
Yamaguti ( 1958 )
transferred it to
Morishitium
. Rudimentary oral sucker present—Zeliff ( 1943 ).
